    {
      "title": "Substitute the shifted input",
      "content": "Since $g(x)=f(x+2)$, replace the input of $f$ with $x+2$:<br/>$$g(x)=8(5)^{x+2}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Separate the exponent",
      "content": "Rewrite $5^{x+2}$ as $5^x\\cdot5^2$:<br/>$$g(x)=8(5^x)(5^2)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Simplify the coefficient",
      "content": "Since $5^2=25$, multiply $8$ by $25$:<br/>$$g(x)=8(25)(5^x)=200(5)^x$$<br/>The answer is <strong>B</strong>."
    }
  ]
